wdi2-ST.INT.ARVL.def:
International inbound tourists (overnight visitors) are the number of tourists who travel to a country other than that in which they usually reside, and outside their usual environment, for a period not exceeding 12 months and whose main purpose in visiting is other than an activity remunerated from within the country visited. When data on number of tourists are not available, the number of visitors, which includes tourists, same-day visitors, cruise passengers, and
crew members, is shown instead.
wdi2-ST.INT.ARVL.name: International tourism
wdi2-ST.INT.ARVL.source: World Tourism Organization, Yearbook of Tourism Statistics, Compendium of Tourism Statistics and data files.
